pageContext.claim: “Millions and millions of people voted for us tonight, and, uh, a very sad group of people is trying to disenfranchise that group of people, and we won't stand for it. We will not stand for it.”
pageContext.analysis: Many more millions voted for Biden. Within a day, Biden had earned more than 4 million more votes than Trump — 72.1 million votes to 68.3 million — though the overall popular vote does not determine the presidential election. By the time the vote was completed, Biden's margin had grown to over 7 million votes. He won 81.3 million votes, or 51.4 percent, compared to Trump's 74.2 million votes, or 46.9 percent.
